                <property name="toolTip">
                 <string>&lt;html&gt;&lt;head/&gt;&lt;body&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt; font-weight:400;&quot;&gt;Select the full path to the &lt;b&gt;config.yaml&lt;/b&gt; file generated by your DeepLabCut project.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt; font-weight:400;&quot;&gt;This file is automatically created by DeepLabCut when you set up a project and contains all essential configuration details, such as defined body parts, training parameters, video references, and model settings.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt; font-weight:400;&quot;&gt;Typically, you can find this file inside your project folder.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt; font-weight:400; font-style:italic;&quot;&gt;Example (Windows): C:\Users\YourName\Documents\DeepLabCut\MyProject\config.yaml&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt; font-weight:400; font-style:italic;&quot;&gt;Example (Linux/Mac): /home/yourname/DeepLabCut/MyProject/config.yaml&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt; font-weight:400; font-style:italic;&quot;&gt;This file is required to correctly interpret pose estimation outputs and ensure compatibility with your trained DeepLabCut model.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
