              </item>
              <item row="4" column="2" colspan="2">
               <widget class="QPushButton" name="standardize_videos_button_video_editing_button">
                <property name="sizePolicy">
                 <sizepolicy hsizetype="Preferred" vsizetype="Preferred">
                  <horstretch>0</horstretch>
                  <verstretch>0</verstretch>
                 </sizepolicy>
                </property>
                <property name="minimumSize">
                 <size>
                  <width>120</width>
                  <height>40</height>
                 </size>
                </property>
                <property name="maximumSize">
                 <size>
                  <width>16777215</width>
                  <height>40</height>
                 </size>
                </property>
                <property name="cursor">
                 <cursorShape>WhatsThisCursor</cursorShape>
                </property>
                <property name="toolTip">
                 <string>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:'Segoe UI'; font-size:9pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:10pt; font-weight:700; color:#2c53a1;&quot;&gt;Standardize Videos (Fix Codecs)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-style:italic; color:#eeeeee;&quot;&gt;This step is not strictly required, but it is highly recommended to ensure scientific data integrity and to maximize processing speed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight:700; color:#a21f27;&quot;&gt;Why is this needed?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Many types of video acquisition software do not save videos in a format suitable for computer vision-based processing. A very common issue is that videos are not reliably seekable, meaning that you may not get the same data when trying to read a particular frame index. This is because many video formats are optimized for realtime playback and save space by reconstructing the image using data in adjacent frames. The consequence is that you may not get the exact same image depending on what the last frame you read was.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight:700; color:#2c53a1;&quot;&gt;What does this do?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Clicking this button performs a high-speed conversion of your videos into a pristine, computer-vision-ready H.264 format with a Constant Frame Rate (CFR).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight:700; color:#ffaa00;&quot;&gt;Performance Boost:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;Because legacy codecs (like MPEG4) do not support modern hardware decoding, they force your CPU to do all the heavy lifting. Standardizing your videos unlocks full Nvidia hardware acceleration, often speeding up your downstream cropping and DeepLabCut processing by 5x to 10x!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:8pt; font-style:italic; color:#999999;&quot;&gt;Note: Your original files will be safely backed up into an 'unwanted_files' subfolder.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;
</string>
                </property>
                <property name="styleSheet">
                 <string notr="true">/* Base button */
QPushButton {
    font: 8pt &quot;Arial&quot;;
    font-weight: bold;

    border: 2px solid #653123;
    border-radius: 8px;

    background-color: #653123;
    color: #FFFFFF;
}

/* Hover (lighter) */
QPushButton:hover {
    background-color: #7A3C2B;
    border: 2px solid #7A3C2B;
}

/* Pressed (darker) */
QPushButton:pressed {
    background-color: #4E261B;
    border: 2px solid #4E261B;
}

/* Disabled (desaturated + lighter) */
QPushButton:disabled {
    background-color: #A89A95;
    border: 2px solid #8C807B;
    color: #E5E5E5;
}</string>
                </property>
